{
  "text": "Similar to MFC, HITS presented by Kleinberg [CITATION_1] aims to discover hyperlinkbased Web communities. The basic assumption behind HITS is that there exist authorities and hubs on the Web, and authorities are often pointed to by hubs that preferentially point to authorities. Based on the mutually reinforcing relationship between authorities and hubs, they developed an iterative method for inferring such authority-hub communities from the Web by computing the principal eigenvectors of two special matrices in terms of the adjacency matrix of the Web. A search engine based on HITS can return the most topic-related pages to users.",
